     1	import spacy
     2	
     3	def spacy_result_to_conll(sentence):
     4	    """
     5	    Generates a dependency parse for the input sentence in the CoNLL-U format.
     6	
     7	    Args:
     8	        sentence (`str`): An input sentence.
     9	    
    10	    Retruns:
    11	        conll_output (`str`): A dependency parse for the input sentence in the CoNLL-U format.
    12	    """
    13	    nlp = spacy.load("en_core_web_sm")
    14	    doc = nlp(sentence)
    15	
    16	    header = ["ID", "text", "LEMMA", "POS", "Tag", "FEATS", "HEAD", "DEPREL", "DEPS", "MISC"]
    17	    conll_output = "{:<5} {:<10} {:<10} {:<6} {:<6} {:<6} {:<6} {:<8} {:<6} {:<6}\n".format(*header)
    18	
    19	    for token in doc:
    20	        row = [
    21	            token.i + 1,  # ID
    22	            token.text,  # FORM
    23	            token.lemma_,  # LEMMA
    24	            token.pos_,  # UPOS
    25	            token.tag_,  # XPOS
    26	            "_",  # FEATS
    27	            token.head.i + 1,  # HEAD
    28	            token.dep_,  # DEPREL
    29	            "_",  # DEPS
    30	            "_"  # MISC
    31	        ]
    32	        conll_output += "{:<5} {:<10} {:<10} {:<6} {:<6} {:<6} {:<6} {:<8} {:<6} {:<6}\n".format(*row)
    33	
    34	    return conll_output
